# MATLAB Economics Research

- Keep each function or script focused on one job: calibration, solution, simulation, or export.
- Prefer functions with explicit inputs and outputs over scripts that rely on the base workspace.
- Name parameter structs, grids, and calibration targets clearly.
- Check convergence and residuals explicitly, and report failure states rather than silently continuing.
- Separate model solution code from plotting or export code when practical.
- Preallocate arrays when loop sizes are known.
- Document frequency conventions, normalization choices, and timing assumptions near the code that uses them.

```matlab
% Bad
load params.mat
solve_model

% Good
results = solve_model(params, grids, options);
```
